===Etymology===
from Greek ''ξύλο'' (k͡sýlo), “wood”, and ''φωνή'' (fōnḗ), “sound”

===Noun===
'''xylophone'''

#a [[musical instrument]] made of wooden slats graduated so as to make the sounds of the scale when struck with a small drum-stick like hammer.
#:''All I know how to play on my xylophone is "Mary Had a Little Lamb". Would you like to hear it?''

